==Old English==
===Spellings===
wæġn, wæġen, wǣn

===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*wagna-'', from Indo-European ''*wegh-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[wagan]] (Dutch [[wagen]]), Old High German [[wagan]] (German [[Wagen]]), Old Norse [[vagn]] (Swedish [[vagn]]).  The IE root is also the source of [[way]] and [[weigh]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /wæjn/

===Noun===
'''wæġn''' ''m''
# a [[wagon]], a [[carriage]]
# the [[Plough]]

===Descendents===
*English [[wain]]

